                <h1>Ultimate Guide: Removing Wallpaper from Drywall</h1>
                <p>To effectively remove wallpaper from drywall, start by carefully peeling off as much as possible. Use a wallpaper removal solution or a mixture of warm water and fabric softener to soak the remaining paper. Apply with a sponge, let it sit, then scrape with a putty knife. Finally, clean any residue with soap and water for a smooth finish.</p>
